    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are looking for a high-ceiling performance today, led by **Gunnar Henderson** (74.65) and **Kyle Tucker** (73.24). **Gunnar Henderson** stands out as the premier play; he faces a favorable matchup against Peter Lambert and benefits from a significant 16% park boost, compounded by a strong 14% platoon edge and the optimal leadoff spot. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker** remains an essential start despite facing a tough arm in Sandy Alcantara, as his elite base projection and favorable order position allow him to maintain high efficiency. **Jacob Wilson** (72.73) and **Josh Lowe** (72.21) round out our top-tier tier, with **Josh Lowe** specifically benefiting from a soft matchup against Fedde and a high-probability SB environment that aligns with our organizational priority on speed.\n\nWe are keeping a close eye on **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (78.22), whose score is bolstered by a substantial BvP edge against Brayan Bello and positive park factors, making him our strongest candidate for a multi-RBI day. Conversely, **Luis Robert Jr.** (49.91) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (49.80) are hovering near the marginal line due to neutral-to-negative platoon dynamics. The most difficult bench decision involved **Josh Jung** (54.61), who was the strongest candidate to crack the lineup; ultimately, the optimizer prioritized the higher defensive and situational efficiency of our core infielders over **Josh Jung**'s baseline, which suffered slightly from a neutral platoon matchup against Eduardo Rodr\u00edguez.\n\nManagement must remain alert regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" status for many of our assets, particularly **Drake Baldwin** and **Liam Hicks**, as any shifts in batting order will directly impact their efficiency scores. While our lineup is optimized for the current projections, we are monitoring potential volatility with **Heliot Ramos** on the bench\u2014though he remains excluded from the starting nine today due to a 40% rain risk in his contest against Cristopher S\u00e1nchez, which effectively neutralized his value relative to our active starters. We are prioritizing stability today to avoid wasting precious game caps on sub-optimal conditions.",
